comment: Only graded on 4 assignments (30% Midterm, 30% Final, 20% Reading Quizzes, 20% Group Project). Extremely dry, boring content, kind of assumes everyone has an advanced level of knowledge even though there are no pre reqs to the class. Exams are unnecessarily difficult - both the midterm and final had to be curved by 20 points each.

Final grade is only based on two exams, reading quizzes, and a group project. The class is pretty difficult, he had to curve the midterm and final for a decent amount of points, think 10-20. The lectures can be boring but he does a decent job teaching, willing to answer questions, and is overall a pretty chill professor.
Class was super easy. One reading quiz a week which was common sense if you read the book. Curves the midterm and final a LOT. Highly recommend for a GE and he was super nice.

Lecture could be dry at times, but I still liked this class. Just a midterm and final (both administered online), final paper, and pop tophat quizzes based on the readings. He has students best interests at heart and everything was pretty straightforward.

Alex was an excellent lecturer. Insightful, even handed, and willing to answer questions and have a discussion. The class was based mostly on the midterms, final and paper, but he gave a generous curve and graded fairly. I really enjoyed this class.

This class is unnecessarily tedious and difficult. Endless amount of policies to choose from to study, and this prof seemingly picks the most boring topics possible. Doesn't give clear guidelines or content of exams, the quizzes don't even match the readings, and was pretentious with occasional out of pocket things said. -900/10, don't recommend.

This class was pretty easy, if you took high school gov you're off to a good start. I really liked Prof Acs, and though I probably could've gotten an A while skipping some lectures, I genuinely enjoyed being there. Classes kind of feel like a casual chat but he does teach the material well. Funny, chill, will lightly make fun of people.

Many questions are completely ambiguous or have conflicting information which makes the midterm luck-based. Everyone ran out of time, average was initially an 80%. Now it's a 78%, and we're confused whether he curved it down? No lecture recs, mandatory attendance, midterms open at 9AM for 1 hour, & no slides released until weeks after his lectures.

Professor Acs is a really great professor. He is clear about what his expectations are for your assignments. There are 2 midterms, 1 final. Lots of extra credit opportunity and he also curves almost all the exams. He is very smart and yet is easy to learn from as he explains things flawlessly. He is also funny and really nice!

Aces clearly loves the information he is teaching, the class had only three test- which he curved and extra credit was able to be given. There was a textbook- but I never bought it. I put this class on the back burner of 18 credit hours- not that it is easy, just never any commitment besides the three exams.

Your grade is determined based on the final and midterm exams. The exams are extremely hard he had to curve grades 12% because a lot of our class failed. Lectures are really boring. Wouldnt recommend this course or teacher. This intro class definitely hurt my gpa. Take with another professor if you can!

The only grade in the class is the midterm and final, which isn't an easy exam, but he does curve it! I would take it with someone else if possible, but have learned a lot. It is an intro level course, but is much harder than that. Other students in my class do not like him, but I do not mind him.

The only grade in the class is the midterm and final, which isn't an easy exam, but he does curve it! I would take it with someone else if possible, but have learned a lot. It is an intro level course, but is much harder than that.

He's a great guy who loves this topic, but you don't actually get through much content in the class because he talks about it all a little too much. Graded by three response papers, two exams, one final paper, and some reading quizzes. You really need to do the reading and it's very unclear exactly what he expects you to do in the papers.

She obviously knows what she is talking about in regards to the class. However, students did not know that much, and she was not super clear in what was expected. Multiple times I got points taken off for things I would have done if I would have been told to do so. Also, attendance "wasn't mandatory", but she did random attendance checks.

She's clear as mud when it comes to everything--almost as if she is writing her dissertation on academic vagueness. Lectures are not mandatory but she throws in all sorts of attendance checks and participation activities, so you better attend. I was excited for the group project but I was stuck doing all of the work and it really dragged on.

Very unreasonable and harsh with grading group work. She would basically laugh us off when we went to her for help/clarification. She's absolutely brilliant and dedicated to her studies but I don't think she understood that her students aren't at the same level of knowledge as she is. She's moving to DC so luckily you probably won't have her.
She gives every opportunity to do well in this class and to communicate with her as an instructor. Highly recommend!

My favorite professor to learn from in 6 years at OSU. The lectures are so clear, so well thought out. The organization of the courses is fantastic. It does involve a good amount of work, but I never felt it was a waste of time or busy work. She makes me regret not choosing epidemiology or biostats as my focus for grad school.

My favorite professor to learn from in 6 years at Ohio State (undergrad + grad school). Her lectures are so clear, her organization is unbeatable, and I genuinely came away from this class feeling confident in everything she taught me. Makes me regret not doing epidemiology. There is a lot of work with the course, but nothing you don't learn from.

My experience with Dr.Andridge was very positive. I really appreciate how she teaches (you do a weekly lab and quizzes and assignments ) so you get plenty of practice before exams. She will also take time to explain concepts and make sure that you understand it by the end of her explanation. I would highly recommend taking any course with her.

Dr. Andridge is a very difficult professor to work with and does not respect her students. When difficult situations arise in the classroom she's been shown to handle them extremely unfairly and without respect and careful consideration. If you're looking for fair treatment and respect from your professor I would not recommend Dr. Andridge.
She is a great professor; gives extremely good feedback. If you work for it, you can easily get an A
Dr. Angel is the Best. Recommend his American Presidency class!

Dr. Angel is extremely considerate and thorough. You know exactly what is going to happen and when it will happen. I knew when I signed up for his class that I would need to miss some days of class and he was very helpful in allowing me to make up missed work and assignments prior to leaving. Anything on tests/quizzes are discussed in class.

I liked taking his class but I have to say it's quite repetitive. Yeah you learn a lot but it's super boring sometimes. You can easily pass the class with an A by just using sparknotes and not reading the 2 hours of homework he wants you to do by the next lecture. But he is very knowledgeable and friendly I liked him overall just kinda boring.

LOVE LOVE LOVED this class. Dr. Angel has the ability to show his students how politics really works, and he does it with absolutely no bias. I took this class thinking that I knew how our government works, and I left the class with a genuine understanding of it. I recommend this class to EVERYONE at OSU Lima, whether it is a requirement or not.
Very knowledgable and helpful. His class requires a lot of reading but it is not hard material.
great instruction

I took his honors poli sci class and it was great. He is very very interested in teaching and def knows what he is talking about. group work helps a lot with class discussion and he hands everything back with a lot of feed back. a great teacher with a lot of experiance, including his own politics book that we worked with in class, def. take him!
Really knows his stuff and interested in teaching. Don't take his class early in the day though, his voice will put you to sleep fast.

Great professor, Dr. Angel is very helpful outside of class. His lectures are very clear, and we did a lot of group work also. The group work really helped with the lectures. Make sure you read the books, because they will help you, especially on the exams. I would highly suggest taking him, he is a great professor, and the class was really good.

I actually took this class a couple years ago, but never did this. Angel is a great prof and a good lecturer. Hes very passionate about the subject and that rubs off on his students. Definitely recommend this class for your GEC requirements.
No Comments
No Comments
interesting - but monotonic...
Genuinely interested in teaching. A lot of class discussion; really made the class more about the students and less about himself.

Dr. Archer is very kind and makes an effort to get to know all of the students. She's very interested in helping students, and the class is easy enough if you do all the assignments. There are online lectures weekly that are used for the quizzes, and a final poster project that builds throughout the semester. I would recommend taking Dr. Archer.

Dr. Arkes was a very good professor. I really had no interest in judgement and decision making before I entered his classroom but now I have a new understanding and respect for the subject matter. The only complaints that I would have would be we did not have a textbook which made things hard. The class is challenging but very interesting.
Very respectful of everyone's questions and comments, makes the topic very interesting. I thought the class would be dull but it actually changed my life! I strongly recommend it.
This is a very interesting class. I definitely learned a lot, but this is also a difficult class. It takes a lot of work, but it's well worth it.
Simply awesome - best professor I ever had.
He's a GREAT teacher, but watch out for the paper at the end of the class. I had to take a LOT of time to research for it. He's a great teacher and it's a great class but don't get lazy!
Arkes is a great guy, he went out of his way to help me find an article that I needed for my research paper.
Definitely keeps the lectures interesting. The readings correlate well with the lectures. I thoroughly enjoyed this class and thought he was really nice.
No Comments

Very good teacher! My favorite psych class I've taken for the past 4 years. The only hard part is that there is a big paper at the end and a cumulative final, but there are many small assigments along the way for the paper so you can't get behind.
He does know his stuff but do not get on his bad side. If you do he will undermine you in a passive aggressive way.

Course material is difficult, but he makes it understandable and interesting. Very helpful. Liberal grader and very fair. Big paper, but you pick the topic. Definitely would take him again...brilliant.
Show up, pay attention, the lectures are in depth but you will learn so much from him. When working on the paper, go to him he will you the feedback you need to pass. He is a great teacher.

Asher is really one of the best at OSU. His tests are tough but fair, the paper is easy if you follow his instructions and go to him for help, and the reading isn't really necessary. The guy is absolutely brilliant and knows an unbelievable amount about OH politics, you will learn a ton!

Having your Ohio Politics class taught by Presdident Gee's Senior Political Advisor is pretty darn awesome! Definitely attend lectures, as Asher has plenty of insightful stories and experience on the subject matter. A TON of reading, but most was relevant and helpful on exams. Attendance, studying and reading are all necessary for an A!

Prof Asher is a very good lecturer. The class is a typical poli sci class, with two midterms that are essay based. Recitation is used to explore interesting topics. Also, there is a requirement to volunteer for a campaign 6-10 hours a week, with a paper due at the end of the quarter. Would definitely recommend prof Asher.

Excellent. His lectures are very interesting, and he is really laid-back. You have to work for six hours per week with a campaign of your choice and write an essay about it. Do not buy the textbooks; you will never even look at them.
I thought Dr. Asher's Ohio Politics class was outstanding. He's the best professor I've had at the university thusfar. And no, it's not impossible to get an A in his class.

Great Prof!! Very entertaining, and very personable. He's biased, and doesn't try to hide it, but will like you no matter your opinions as long as you share your opinions. We barely used the textbooks, and the exams weren't bad if you paid attention in class. I learned a lot in this class!

Independents and third-party supporters beware: this guy often confuses facts with opinions, whether or not his students realize it. He is quite biased against certain candidates and parties, yet some of the things he says contradict with his own biased statements-- apparently not enough to get him to change his mind.. What a letdown.

LOVED his class. Learned so much! He made it interesting by actually "talking" to the class and not lecturing in a monotone class. He has a sense of humor about things,but if ur not a "favorite" don't expect to be called on. My favorite PS class ever.
Dr. Asher is a wonderful professor. No political science degree is complete without taking his classes. Lectures were interesting, and I learned a great deal from him.
Great lectures, you will learn a good deal about Ohio Politics.
Good prof... easy class didn't buy the books and go an A. Just show up and you'll be fine.

Great class. If you are actually a PoliSci major this is a great class and you will learn a lot. This is a high level class so no, he is not going to hold your hand and give you outlines and essay questions but it is stupid to presume that an instructor should do so. It's called college, not high school. Overall, a good class with lots of info.
Really, great guy, great class. Those claiming he is biased are absolutely ridiculous, you can be conservative as you want and the guy is respectful. Easy, fun, and informative. Take him if you can.

Herb Asher is the best professor at OSU! His lectures are interesting, informative, and full of relevant anecdotes. He loves what he teaches and he cares for his students. If you get to know him, he will make a great mentor and will take the time to meet with you and offer advice to you. I always looked forward to going to his classes!

decent professor and a funny guy, although you don't really learn a lot in his class. exams are not fun at all, since he doesn't provide an outline of terms or anything to that extent in the way of preperation. overall it's not that difficult of a class, just be prepared to spend time working outside of class doing volunteering, surveys, etc.
Do not even bother unless you are a democrat. Very Very liberal. Biggest name dropper in the world. Who the hell cares who Vern Riffe is, I sure don't. HAVE FUN!!!!

Excellent professor! If you want to learn about Ohio and her politics, there is no better professor to have than Herb Asher; itâ€™s definitely a class that you don't want to miss! His lectures are always informative, relevant and never boring. On a separate note, I read one of his books for another class (Polling and the Public: What Every Citize
Straight forward class: midterm, final, and paper
Good lectures. Go to class in order to do well on the tests. Grades papers slightly hard. Knows his Ohio policitcs quite well.

Prof. Baker is the most grounded and personable professor I've ever had. I have ADHD and I can confidently say that his lectures are amazingly engaging, I've never been bored in his class. He exudes so much passion through his lectures that it's frankly hard to not do well in his class. Overall, one of the best learning experiences in my life.

I had Professor Baker twice for 2 different classes, 1101 and 3460. Both times he was very enjoyable to have. He is very knowledgeable about the material that is given and the classes were both very interesting but you need to come to class and be ready to learn. Highly recommend having him.

I loved this class with Gia. They are so enthusiastic and have so much experience to share. There is a good amount of reading that I struggled to keep up with but it rarely impacted my ability to participate. Participating in their class is so thought-provoking and you can really get a lot out of it. Gia will challenge you, and it rocks!

Gia is one of those professors I will never forget. Not only are they well educated in the topic they are lecturing on, but it is very apparent that they are passionate about it as well. Their lectures are very fast paced, but that just further illustrates that they love what they do. I would take them again in a heart beat!

Dr. Basta is a true asset to Ohio State. His lectures are interesting. He has a great sense of humor, enjoys teaching, and his experience outside of the classroom really helps you apply what your learning. Show up for class, make note cards of the lectures, and you'll get an A. He assigned 3 math oriented assignments and 15 half page briefs.

Dr. Basta is an excellent professor. He seems to genuinely enjoy teaching. His lectures are interesting. I would absolutely take him again. The tests are taken directly from the lecture notes. There is a little bit of math involved in the class but this is to be expected from a chemistry class. Understand logarithms. He's funny and cares.

Dr. Basta is a great guy. His soil chemistry class is a difficult class, but if you come to class everyday and engage with him during lecture you will be fine. Visit him during office hours if you ever have questions and he will help you out and ease any fear you may have.
Great guy. Very clear and easy to understand.

Professor Baum was amazing. If you are seriously considering law school, I definitely recommend taking one of his classes. The entire class is very lecture and exam heavy, but if you truly engage in class and with the material, you will do just fine. I learned more in this class than I learned in any other political science classes combined.

Lawrence is a great guy and the best professor in this department. I have taken his two classes and I can say they will humble you. Not an easy A at all. Go for every class and write down every word he says. Highly recommend if you see law school in your future. It is very likely you will not get an A in this class. If that matters to you skip this

Great guy. Loved 4136 with him, so I took this class. Anyone with any interest in the Supreme Court should take him; you will learn so much. This class wasn't as good; I'd already learned about a lot of material in his other course. Still valuable research and writing skills. He provides copious guidelines for the paper. Do that and you'll be ok.

This is one of the most interesting classes I have ever taken. While the class is very difficult (beware if you just want a grade booster), he is really passionate about the subject and I learned a lot more about the Supreme Court. The papers are long and difficult to write (20 page final paper), but it will turn out alright if you put in the work!

If you have a chance to take a class with Dr. Baum. Do it. He is incredibly kind and cares so much for his students. Any and all of your questions will be answered in depth and he is very accommodating. The content can be a lot but if you follow the syllabus, you'll be fine

Dr. Baum is a fantastic professor. The final paper is long, but you will build up to it in your other two papers. By the end of the class you will have a comprehensive understanding of the court and a paper as a reference for your writing abilities. He does his best to connect with all students. I highly suggest taking even if you are not honors.

By far one of my favorite professors at OSU. His class had challenging material, but none of the assignments or exams are extremely difficult and he is great about implementing feedback. He also gave an easy extra credit assignment. I wish I had taken more classes with him while at OSU.

My favorite class I've ever taken was the one I took with him. He doesn't take attendance (though he notices those who show up) but GO TO CLASS. He's a great lecturer and if you know your lectures and cases you'll be fine . Sit towards the front to be one of Larry's favorites. You'll just want him to like you. It'll just make you feel good.

Dr. Baum was incredible, a 6/5. He always assumed he explained something wrong instead of getting mad at students for not understanding, he let us be curious without letting "poli sci kids" pull us off on a tangent, and he pulled from current events to teach material. The class was tough, lecture-heavy, and lots of reading for sure, but worth it.

Dr. Baum is my favorite professor I have had so far at OSU. He cares so much for his students and is very passionate about the content he teaches. This class is tough but he works with you and makes sure that you learn. Although I received a B I believe I learned more in his course than any of the others I took this term.

Professor Baum is one of the most kind, helpful professors I have ever had. The class is comprised of just three essays. They are 5, 10, and 20 pages and the 20 page is worth 70% of your grade. It seems intimidating, but he prepares you really well to do it and you will learn a ton. No attendance, but if you miss class you're screwed for the essays

Prof. Baum is the best professor Ive ever had at OSU as far as what I learned in the class but the class was not easy! I loved the content, but there were only 3 exams, completely essay-based and timed. I had to rewatch lectures several times to get all the information at times. It was tough, but worth it. I feel like I know so much more now!

Professor Baum is a fantastic instructor but also an incredibly tough grader. Class is made up entirely of exams, so don't fail any because otherwise, you'll fail the course. He also offers little to no extra credit, so don't forget to prep for exams because they're your only source of redemption.

Dr. Baum is one of the most kind and caring professors I've had at OSU. He does not use lecture slides, which is an adjustment at first, but is very engaging in class. His course was no cakewalk and the material bordered on dull at times, but it wasn't bad if you pay attention and study for exams.

Dr. Baum is one of the best professors at OSU. Truly one of the nicest, most knowledgeable, and helpful professors I've had. Not an easy A but wont make you cry yourself to sleep. Not an overwhelming amount of work but covers a lot of material. He does not use any notes and lecture is completely oral, which is an adjustment but helped me focus.

Baum is one of my favorite professors at OSU because he cares a lot about his students. I learned a lot in this course, and not just surface-level content but a deeper understanding of the Supreme Court. I recommend recording lectures because while they are engaging, they are long, and they are pretty much your only source of class content.

Professor Baum's class isn't "easy" but you will learn a lot. I truly feel lucky to have been able to take 2 classes with him. You won't meet a professor at OSU that's more knowledgeable, kind, and caring. And he's hilarious.

He does not use any kind of slides or another presentation tool in class, he talks at you for 1:20 straight. This class was also graded solely on exams, which is not something I enjoy. I found recording the lectures to be somewhat helpful, but overall was not a fan of him at all. He is also confusing, sometimes going back on what he said before.

Professor Baum was likely the most knowledgable and accessible professor I've had. The class was comprised of 3 papers, all research-based. However, you're given the time and resources to get it done, and he is there every step of the way to help. I wish I had another class with him because he is one of the kindest and smartest professors I've had.

Lawrence Baum might be the best professor I've had at OSU. While the class is totally lecture based, the way he presents the material is so interesting and you can tell how much he knows and loves what he does. I would suggest studying early because if you do the topic guides and know them well, you'll be fine on the exams!

Prof. Beck's course is largely statistical and focuses on the kinda stuff most political science students probably already know (at least in a loose sense). As such, lectures are quite boring and most of the information can be gathered from skimming the slides he provides. He's terribly dry but very smart, so you can't really help but respect him.

He's a great professor. The lectures are dull and sooooo long, and you'll definitely fall asleep. He really knows what he's talking about, though, and you really have no excuse for not doing well if you show up. Lots of readings, but skimming them is more than enough.
Great teacher

Mr.Beck is a great teacher who knows his stuff. He is liberal(check fec.gov for who he's donated to) but does a great job hiding it. DO THE READINGS.the exams are multiple choice/essay. he gives the possible 6 essay questions in advance. My advice would be to draft the essays out in advance after doing readings,so that you're not doing the night B4

Amazing professor! Creates a great balance between professionalism and fun (humor) in the classroom. Material is very relevant to current affairs. He's always very accessible, and is always willing to help. He's a Prof. Emeritus, so take a class with him while he's still at the University!

Dr. Beck is extremely passionate about the field of Political Science and is very knowledgable about the subject matter. Yes he does tend to stray off topic, but the majority of his lectures are interesting and informative. He references the books and they are extremely helpful to study for the midterms with.

Mr. Beck is very knowledgeable and enthusiastic about political parties. He is a great teacher, but sometimes his lectures can be a bit dry, boring, and repetitive. The two exams he gives are 25 multiple choice questions each with a long essay response as well. He also has you do a research paper that makes up a big portion of your grade.
Professor Beck is incredibly well knowledge and generally a nice person. I highly recommend him.

Really great professor, one of the best I've ever had. Very friendly and communicates really well with the students. The class wasn't too challenging but wasn't easy, and I learned a lot. Highly recommended.

Awesome guy. Class is easy and he really knows his stuff. Always gives you room to voice your opinion, and grades you not on your opinion, but how you back it up and how well you know the material. Exams are straightforward and simple and he puts in a lot of cool stories and opinion pieces in his lectures. Definitely recommend him.

Prof Beck is a really great teacher. Helpful with anything you could ever need help with. Instant responses to emails, go out of his way for office hours etc. Lecture can be boring at times, but a lot of political anecdotes. Paper is fairly easy and exams are straight forward. Gives you essays ahead of time to study.

Great teacher. Clearly knew the topic, researched any questions he did not know the answer to. Grades very fairly, the essay was easy to get a good grade on. Attendance not required, but can be used to bump grade up if you are close. Overall great teacher, if you have the option, take him!
Professor Beck is a good guy. His class is easy, but you learn a lot. I thought the material was interesting - and you could see that he enjoyed teaching it.

Dean Beck is a good teacher. He is very informative and does a great job relating the topics to more recent elections. The class can get boring at times, but it is very interesting. The class is not too difficult and the paper topic is very interesting.
very nice and interesting! Explains everything clearly
Very nice man, interesting class; genuinely decent human being and very bright man.
Easy but boring.
No Comments
Great sense of humor.
No Comments

I enjoyed this class. He posts slides on carmen, but does add more informations during lecture. While lecture is not mandatory, I would recommend attending for the extra information. He has lots of stories that relates with the material. The test are from both lecture and books. It's not a bad class to take and has a nice curve.

I really enjoyed this class. Dr. Beck is a little disorganized but his lectures are interesting. His tests are from both the book and the lecture material and he loves testing on statistics. If you're interested in psychopathology you'll like the class. I recommend it.

His statistics are a lot of times way off but you need to know them for the exams anyways. You can get an A fairly easily if you read the book and attend class....but if you are really interested in Psychology- his class is frustrating because lecture doesn't relate to Adjustment at all.

Dr. Beck is a very nice guy who is interested in his field BUT I would caution you not to take the class. He uses outdated materials and information. If you choose to take the course make sure that you read the textbook cover to cover and write down every random statistic he says in class.

This class is not as bad as it may seem. He is a practicing psychologist so he lectures on what he thinks is interesting and then you are responsible for what is in the book for the exam. He loves statistics so pay close attention to them while your taking book notes. He also gives a pretty big curve which helps a lot. I got an A fairly easily.

The tests in this class were ridiculous, they are made up of totally random questions from the book. I found the lecture parts of the test to be quite easy, but his lectures are boring and the research is outdated. There is no new info to be learned in this class if you have already taken counseling psych and abnormal psych.

Dr. Beck was extremely spacey, disorganized and dull. His lectures sometimes have information that is incorrect and misleading. He relies HEAVILY on insignificant details from the book. If you read the book then that part of the test is fine, but the lecture section is ridiculous. The paper, however, was easy.

Dr. Beck is really nice but I would caution everyone interested in taking his Psych 681 course. First, he lectures little to nothing from the book and you are responsible for the book and lectures on the tests (they're often opposing information). He is spacey, extremely unorganized, his tests don't make sense, & has lectured incorrect information.

The class was interesting and he was a pretty good lecturer. A lot of people didn't come to class but if you go to lecture and read the book thoroughly it is easy to get an A. He doesn't cover the reading in class so you have to be motivated to do it on your own. He seemed like a really nice guy and had a lot of good stories from his clinical work.

He makes mistakes on his own exams, makes you choose between what he says in class and what the book says, and if that's not enough, you spend half the time trying to figure out what the questions are asking. Nice guy, but extremely spacey, making for an unreliable professor.

Dr. Beck is obviously a caring man, but he is just not the best teacher. The class was unorganized and it was hard to get questions answered. You must read the book very closely! and the topics assigned for reading will be different than that discussed in lecture. The class is so frustrating it's not worth taking even if you're highly interested.

The class is not hard if you life cold hard stats. Half of exam comes from the book (which you never go over and is indep study) and lectures that are based on date he has found on diff. subjects. He comes off anxious and is pretty scatter-brained, unprepared. His off the cuff style does not work. 3 exams and a an easy paper. Take only if needed.
This professor constantly generalizes about disorders, uses outdated research, and is super terrible at writing exams. good luck, i would not recommend him, he needs to retire

I just recently graduated from OSU and this was one of my favorite classes...and it was even in the early morning. Dr. Beck had some really interesting things to say and if you went to class, he gave hints for the tests. Very intelligent, educated and fair prof. Hightly recommended!
I like the guy but the test are tough.

This was my first class as a non-trad student after being out of school for 8 years. I found Dr. Beck's lectures interesting and relevant to the real world. He uses a lot of stories which were interesting to me. Half of the tests are from the text, so there is a lot of reading involved. If you go to class and read the text, you can get an A.

Attendence is not mandatory but I would definitely recommend going, since part of the exams come from the book. Dr. Beck is an amazing professor. He knows his material and is very passionate about all of it. Lectures were very interesting. I don't get up for many 9 am classes, but I hardly ever missed his!
No Comments

This is a must to take psych class!! Dr. Beck makes an hour and 48 min seem like half an hour. His lectures are outstanding, applicable to real world, nothing obscure. But careful!His tests have a lot of stats and are long. Even so, its a well balanced class and very informative and entertaining. Overall is great, study and you can easily get an A.

This man has no buisiness being a college proffesor.
  If a student asks a question which he doesn't know the answer to, he just guesses, often times wrongly.
  The subject matter is very easy to master, yet it is nearly impossible to get an A. This is because his tests include many random and irrelavent statistics from the text book.

Dr. Bellair is an excellent professor. He really cares about his student's success. His course is very well-organized and he does as much as he can to make a course of this difficulty accessible to his students. The only note was some of the readings were really long, over 100 pages, and could have easily been assigned with only the abstract.

Very, very boring lectures. Stays on the same slide for an hour. Attendance does matter because you do writing assignments in each class. Very boring and drawn out talks but easy class. Tests aren't too bad as long as you study.

Overall a pretty easy class if you do the readings and attend class to complete critical thinking written assignments (1-2 paragraphs). Lectures are extremely boring. I think this class could be really interesting if taught by a different professor. If you want to attend jailprison tours, don't schedule class after this one.

Overall solid professor. Class can seem a bit slow at times and he isn't the best with powerpoint, but he certainly knows his stuff. If you attend class, pay attention, and do the in class writings, it's hard to get a bad grade. Exams are easy, and he look like Tobias from Arrested Development without a mustache. Solid dude
Boring. Bad use of powerpoint.

I actually enjoyed this class with Professor Bellair. His exams are pretty easy as long as you read the chapters and attend class. Complete the critical thinking questions and it is hard to get a bad grade in this class. He knows what he's talking about and invites you on jail visits with his higher level classes! I'd take a class with him again
Extremely boring teacher, speaks mono-tone the whole time. Makes harder to understand than it should be.

The previous two post say it well. He stands in front of the class and simply lectures from the book, he's more than boring, and he makes the class harder than it needs to be. He does provide his slides but not until a couple days before the test. He gives absolutely NO review and you're on your own for the tests. Very disappointed in this teacher.

He is unresponsive to e-mails if you need to miss class, so you don't even know if he received them. He doesn't give out study guides. He says read the chapters assigned & study the slides which are like 80 slides. He doesn't post the ppts before hand so you give up taking notes. He says you can arrange to change your final if needed but doesn't.

3 MC tests. Seemed to stretch for material on a few of the questions. Lectures were pretty boring. Had 1-3 opinion questions that you had to hand in at the end of each class. Just hand in something and you are good. These were worth a solid % of the grade and worth the effort.

Dr. Belury is a very nice professor and really wants students to do well-- she even brought snacks to lecture for students multiple times! Her exams are almost exactly the same questions as her quizzes, so make sure to review those often. There is a weekly online quiz but otherwise exams are just quizzes and exact lecture slides. Not a bad class!
Belury is an extremely boring lecturer, however her exams are made up of exactly what is posted on the slides, so memorize these! You do not need to attend lecture to get a good grade in this class.

Group work is terrible, but Dr. Bengal makes it bearable! This class was very challenging, but Dr. Bengal was there to support us every step of the way. He gives wonderful feedback, and his great sense of humor helps numb the pain when that feedback is negative. He's quite literally an award-winning instructor, so take his classes!

I'm writing this to those of you who attend the first day of class and think, "Wow, this guy sounds so annoying." I thought the same thing on the first day, but I was quickly humbled. Steven is the funniest professor I've had at OSU and he can thoroughly relate the content to the students. He actually teaches and I felt prepared for every exam.

Absolutely loved Steven Bengal as a professor. Literally, the best professor I've ever had hands down. His exams can be vigorous but his class is an absolute must-take, a professor I will never forget.

Dr. Bengal is one of the best professors I have had at OSU. Funny, engaging, and eccentric. Cheat sheets for exams, but make sure you go to class and pay moderate attention because the slides are not self-explanatory.

He's an eccentric and funny guy with excellent music taste. Initially, I was intimidated and scared for my wellbeing in this class, but because he's very good at explaining and teaching, I ended up doing very well. He also gives good feedback if you meet with him during office hours.

Super interesting and eccentric guy. His voice is really funny to listen to. Explains the materials very clearly and tries to answer questions all the time. Even though data analysis seems like a dull class he actually makes it a lot more engaging. Would recommend taking any of his classes.

I really enjoyed this class, and though I may not have always understood the material, Dr. Bengal was more than willing to help with any questions I had. He may talk incredibly fast but I guess he's just excited about the material. Also, he might be a stand up comedian in his spare time (need confirmation on this)

11/10 My favorite professor EVER. I hate college, but looked forward to his class every day. He wants students to succeed, actually learn, and treats you like a colleague. His assignments were fun to do (I know, it sounds like a reach,) exams are fair (plus cheat sheet!,) and lectures are top tier. TAKE HIS CLASS TAKE HIS CLASS TAKE HIS CLASS!!!
Literally the best professor I've ever had. He's super funny and it's easy to get an A in the class if you do the homework and pay a moderate amount of attention. Couldn't recommend him more.

A very funny professor who always asks us to "bombard" him with questions and is very quick to respond to emails. He provides full and short lectures on each chapter and puts an emphasis on individual exploration. We had a weekly quiz, discussion posts, questions, journal entry/ activity, and a quiz make-up activity with no exams or tests.

professor bengal is soo funny and makes sure that he is available for students whenever they need. it's very clear that he genuinely cares about teaching and his students. the course load is heavy and confusing at times but very interesting. if you're confused about something, he provides great explanations and will clear things up. def recommend

Super funny guy. Lectures aren't mandatory but are never boring - I would recommend attending but he posts abbreviated recorded lectures that are super helpful as well. His tests can be a bit difficult, though - it's sometimes hard to tell exactly what you need to know versus what is extra information. Regardless, he's wildly entertaining.

I love Doctor Bengal. He is kind but also extremely hilarious in his classes. His mixture of self-deprecation as well as his beautifully crafted power points make him my favorite professor I have had yet. Though the lectures are not attendance-mandatory, you don't want to miss them (especially for his random tangents).

For Halloween, he dressed up as Steve from Blue's Clues and all of us collectively spent the lecture trying to figure out if he was in costume or not, because it wasn't far from how he dresses daily.
 
 11/10 would attend a lecture of his about paint drying.

I don't do rate my professors, but he deserves an awesome rating. The funniest professor and one who cares about his students. He's always asking us for questions and when we ask them he is so happy to answer them. I hope he stays as a professor for a long time because he can make learning fun.

Dr. Bengal is funny & relatable, but I did not like his course, he's unprofessional and swears a lot, and although the tests are relatively easy, the format rubbed me the wrong way. Plus, when I took his class, I missed a thing or a religious holiday, and he wouldn't let me make it up. That assignment was the difference between an A- and B+ for me.

Dr. Bengal is an amazing professor!! I took another one of his course in AU 2021 and I absolutely loved it. Dr. Bengal is amazing at lecturing and he has a way of making sure that you remember the material being taught. Although the exams can be challenging, he is always open to help during his office hours. Definitely recommend!!

Professor Bengal is a very swell guy. I would say lectures are mandatory if you want to have success in this class, especially if you do not have a background in data. I did not know much going in, but I feel pretty confident moving forward because of this course. It's not easy material but I feel lucky I had Dr Bengal to help.

This was by far my favorite class this semester. Dr. Bengal is super engaged in the teaching material, funny and has high standards for students. Homework, projects and exams were challenging but fair, and I learned a lot from them (they did not feel like mindless busy work). 100% recommend this class and Dr. Bengal.

Dr. Bengal is extremely knowledgeable in the topics he teaches and is very generous with extra credit opportunities. The course itself is test heavy (4 exams) but his are not cumulative and they're over less than 5 subjects each. Bengal is very enthusiastic and encourages students to ask questions to make sure they understand the material!

Not a very engaging professor, but the class is easy. Powerpoints are straight from the book and tests are straight froom the powerpoints..do not buy book! You can find it at the library reserves. Only 3 tests, with the lowest dropped. Grades are curved at the end..interesting material!
A very good professor - I really enjoyed attending his lectures. He's extremely knowledgeable on this subject and is genuinely interested in teaching. Awesome prof, awesome class!

Terrible terrible terrible terrible professor!!!! I can't even explain how much I hated his class. I am very interested in this topic and he made me hate it. Sitting through his classes is the worst experience ever. He speaks incredibly slowly and in a monotone voice and does absolutely nothing for his students. Never goes over tests. AVOID!!!!!!!!

The material is tough, but if you pay CLOSE attention during lecture you should do okay. I'm into this topic so it was probably a bit more interesting for me. He's kind of witty, explains things pretty well for such a complex topic.

There was a lot of talk about neurotransmitters and whatnot, which I wasn't prepared for and his monotone voice made lectures kind of painful to sit through; however,if you study the powerpoints he posts on carmen, you will do well in the class. Also, if you do well on the first two exams, you are done for the quarter!
very interesting, lot of material, grades are curved
Great class--great prof

Definitely a lot harder then it seems. A lot of memorizing technical drug names and history of drug use. Tricky test questions and a TON of material to learn. Does not give +/- only A,B,C,D. Test averages in my class were low 70%. It's also really hard to listen to his voice during class and he goes really quick through the slides. AVOID!!

This class should be named Into to Neuropharmacology. Avoid if you are dumb about Psychiatry and drugs. You'll be memorizing pill names and what receptors they hit. I got a B by looking at the powerpoints the night before. that's only because of my previous intrest in crazy meds. Tough class for most, although heavily curved.
Best class ever.
Great professor, got me interested in this topic and now I'm going to graduate school!
Totally awesome class. Best professor I ever had.
This class should be taught online. There is no reason to go to class. All he does is read directly from the slides. His exams are hard... but his curve in the end is nice. Lectures are VERY boring!

Interesting material. DO NOT BUY BOOK!! You will never open it. His powerpoints come straight from book and test question come straight from powerpoints. Class becomes a bit boring after awhile. Best 2 out of 3 on your test grades. Failry hard class. I still recommend it.

He LITERALLY reads right from the powerpoint slides, so if it's in outline form, don't expect him to make clear sentences and explain further then what is stated on the slide. slides posted online, study from those. grade is based off 2 out of 3 tests. You drop your lowest test. easy if you study the slides that he tells you to for the tests.

Another class where the only grades are a 50% midterm and a 50% final. I hate that. I don't think there was any curve so if you moderately screw one up, well, you are kinda just screwed in general. He seems like a nice guy but after a week you will probably get bored of his lectures and just stop going. Just download/study from the powerpoints.

He wasn't the most well organized prof, but lectures are interesting and he fosters discussion very well. Tests were difficult, if you didn't study. He is very willing to help, but you have to ask for it first! Just because you didn't study and didn't get an A doesn't make it a bad class or him a bad prof.
So disappointed. He is so unclear and the tests are hard!
Watch out for this guy. He only does 2 grades - a midterm and final - but they're so hard! The class was called psychology of drugs and behavior, yet I have not seen any behavior aspects yet.
I LOVED this professor. She extremely helpful with any questions you may have, and she really cares for her students. She is AWESOME!

Dr. Betz is absolutely amazing. She is friendly and funny and I actually enjoyed lectures. Material isn't hard to deal with and there's no textbook, 3 exams worth 60pts each and a couple small assignments. I had her for Psych 300 as well, I'd recommend her for any class. She's caring, considerate, and understanding. I can't say enough. She's great
Dr. Betz is the one of the nicest professors I've ever had. I would take her again if i could...her TA Hye Bin is a tough grader though. 300 is an easy class, an easy A.
Dr. Betz is the one of the nicest professors I've ever had. I would take her again if i could...he TA Hye Bin is a tough grader though. 300 is an easy class, an easy A.

Good teacher, great person. Willing to go above and beyond to help students. Left me a note on my homework asking if I wanted any advice on applying to graduate schools, without me asking her beforehand.

Dr. Betz is SUCH a nice lady!! This class is tough though, and there is no book, so you pretty much just have your lecture slides and notes to go by. I would recommend attending lecture even though the subject matter can be very dry. Study hard and you'll do fine. I really recommend this class to psych students who want to go to grad school!

Dr. Betz is ALWAYS there to help and will work with you if you ask her to. She does make semi-frequent mistakes on her powerpoint slides etc. but if you are confused she will clear the confusion for you. Class is hard but if you need help ASK and you will be fine.
Has no clue what she's doing. She spends more time correcting her mistakes and rushing through material than actually explaining the material. A straight Stats class would be more helpful.

If you go to class and pay attention, I don't see how you could not do well. Though i did not personally find the subject matter to be interesting, class was bearable and attendance (while not mandatory) will really help you, because a lot of what is said in class is helpful in understanding and learning the material, and is included on the exams.

Class dragged on a little but Nancy made it fun. Grade is determined from 3 hw short hw assignments, a survey, 2 midterms, and a comprehensive final. I didn't look at the book once and I got a B+ in the class. Print out the notes, go to lecture, and you will have no problem. Also, her TA is a very sweet girl who is very helpful.
Terrible. Her lectures and notes drag on forever. The TA was awful as his e-mails and exams were riddled with poor grammar and contradictions. This class was a complete waste of time.

Dr. Betz is cool! I picked up this class last minute after dropping something else and I'm really glad I did because it was not only surprisingly interesting but personally enriching (you get to take career and personality tests). She's really clear and helpful too and has an amusing dry humor. I would take anything else she teaches.
Dr. Betz is awesome. She's funny and adorably awkward if I weren't graduating I'd try to take more classes from her. Doesn't make you buy a book either!
Very sweet woman. Extremely helpful. Decently interesting class.
Amazing teacher! Keeps lectures interesting and is so extremely helpful in making sure you understand everything!!!

take your next class with prof betz!! she's awesome...always ends class 15 mins early, puts all notes up on power point. only 3 homework assignments and 3 exams. the homework was quite easy, and the exams are all 50 mc questions. her wording can be a bit misleading, but if you get less than a B you're an idiot

Extremely lenient on tests, never gave out homework assignments, and very intellectual on the material. The classes were somewhat boring, but if you made an effort, she'd make sure you got a good grade no matter what.

Dr. Betz is awesome! I only took this class because I knew it was good for grad school prep, but now I love psych testing! I would recomend this class or any of her classes to anyone. She's a great professor and really funny. I always looked forward to her lectures!
I loved this class!
Great job! Learned a lot in this course. The atmosphere was supportive, and discussion topics and presenters were excellent!
exellent teacher. very clear and organized as he managed to make research ethics interesting. very fair grader.

As long as you read the text or go to lecture, the tests are cake. I went to lecture more than half the time, but it wasn't really necessary. He was pretty funny and the lectures were not bad at all. Do the 3 hw assignments just in case you bomb a test. He doesnt curve your grade, so you get what you get. Great professor though.

As many others have stated, not the most exciting material, but not the worst, either. He does try and throw in a few anecdotes (many about his cat or his wife) to try and make the material relevant. But, when he asks questions (during lecture) he will only agree if you give the answer he wants. Overall, not too painful. Notes are posted online

Pretty good teacher. The class itself is pretty boring but it isn't difficult. Going to class def makes it a lot easier. He gives an opportunity for extra credit that can really help your grade if you do it.

No matter who teaches this class it's going to be a boring class. Dr. Billings tries to make it as interesting as possible. He cracks jokes, and tells interesting stories. It's not too bad. Him and his TA helped me a lot in their office. They will be happy to go over exams with you, and explain anything.

This class was bad, I had to drop it! The information is sooo boring and Dr. Billings was a very stiff teacher. I felt like he wasn't approachable at all. He told us to refer all questions to the TA! Tests are soo hard. Only good thing about the class was the optional surveys or paper for 50 points extra credit. Dont take unless life depends on it.

Dr. Billings is a hard teacher. I would not recommend him. When he asks questions in class and students answer the question wrong he puts them down and makes them feel dumb. He does offer extra credit though, and the homeworks are not that hard. Watch out for the tests they can be killers.

Pretty hard class but totally doable, but like someone else said, it's extremely easy to get the 50 bonus points, and they do matter since your grade is out of 1000. I thought the class was extremely boring, and this is the first class I have ever taken which you could definitely get an A without going to class; Everything you need is online.
Good prof. Clear when explaining course material. Very helpful. Worth taking!

He is by far the most effective teacher I have had. Regardless of the material, he does a really good job explaining. I actually learned everything in class just my listening to him. Really good at explaining things.
Tricky class, make sure you understand his testing style and what he thinks is important. He does give extra credit to help if you didn't do so hot on an exam, but exams aren't easy.
This class wasn't the hardest but it wasnt the easiest...the tests werent too hard but the paper was a pain. The class was soooo boring and i'm suprised I made it as much as I did!
The class is really boring but really easy. Just read the book and the notes and you will be fine on the tests. Can get an easy 50 bonus points which makes getting a good grade even easier.

made lectures very interesting considering the material. homeworks very easy & offers easy extra credit. do need to spend some time studying for exams though. overall really good prof. would take another class with him again.
Billings was not the most exciting guy, but he was very helpful and the class was pretty easy. Just don't take it in the morning, or you will never go to class.

You can tell he's genuinely interested in the stuff he teaches. Unfortunately the material is still very boring. He puts all the notes online so going to class is purely optional and it really won't hurt your grade to skip as long as you read the notes before the midterm

The material is dull, but easy to understand. He gives you the notes online. 50 bonus points if you do some surveys. I thought this class was much easier than psych 100. If I recall correctly something like 75% of the class got C+ or above.
He is kind of arrogant and extremely boring- class not recommended.
The material was horribly boring, but he actually made in enjoyable. He has a great sense of humor. He gives you every opportunity to do well.
Great teacher! Tests are all essay, but he grades them very fairly. But bring a pillow on presentaion days, that's a bore!
Great professor. She takes her time to explain everything.

Her class was interesting and went by pretty fast. We had plenty class discussions but never put anyone on the spot if they didn't want to contribute. Attendance is important, its worth it anyway. Only one paper, there is a lot of reading for short quizzes, easy to pass them. Exams are mult choice but rather long. Over all I would take her again.

This is my favorite professor so far. She is so wonderful and has an amazing personality. She is always willing to help us. I lov going to each of her classes. She always makes everything so engaging.

She's an amazing professor, gives lots of reading, however she goes over all assigned texts in details during lectures, listens to student input, she is always there to help, always emails back and is polite and professional.
Awesome professor. You put in the time and effort, she will do everything she can to help you succeed.
Great instructor

Wonderful professor - clear, concise, and really good at conveying the the material and making it relative. She will go out of her way to help any student who is putting forth a legitimate effort. I highly recommend her!

Dr. Bobbitt-Zeher is an amazing professor! She is very clear on what she teaches and everything on her exams is covered in class. Attend class and make sure to read the readings assigned. Dr. B-Z is very helpful and really makes class enjoyable. This is a definite class to take.
She really enjoys what she teaches helping interest you in the material.
Great professor! Do the readings, pay attention and go to class and you'll do fine! She has real passion for sociology.
Definately Recommend!
One of the best professors I have had the pleasure of being in class with.
Best teacher I've ever had.
Her Sociology of Education class is very enlightening and interesting. She is very enthusiastic about her work and is very encouraging. Read the assigned material and show up to class.

Dr. Bobbitt-Zeher is an amazing professor! Make sure you study your notes and READ!!!!! A LARGE majority of your grade is based on reading and class participation..so go to class!! Also, she offers a lot of extra credit. Overall, she makes the class fun and entertaining. Just study your notes, come to class, and read and you will pass. I promise.

Mr. Bonds is tough grader, he gives a 3 papers throughout the semester and a topic and even if you follow the topic he will grade like he is an English professor. He counts and deducts points even if one word is misspelled. He does not give extra credit assignments. He expects perfection right away, instead of teaching how to get there.

Professor Bonds was a very tough grader, he looks for specific answers in his assignments. He assigned multiple quizzes throughout the week and a essay with them every other week. His lectures weren't all that great either. He provides the book readings on blackboard- that was the only plus from his class.

There was a lot of reading but it was not necessary. Could retake most quizzes an unlimited number of times. Directions for papers were sometimes unclear, but she was very good at responding to emails in a timely manner and answered questions well. She is a very easy grader.

Dr. Bowen is a really great professor. Her class was really interesting, interactive, and you can tell she's really passionate about what she does. She's also extremely nice; I was 0.02% away from a solid A in her class and didn't realize you could ask for a bump until the end of the next semester. She bent over backwards and bumped me anyway.

Professor Bowen is a decent professor at OSU Mansfield. She remains unbiased in the politics class, even though her opinion on the matter is clear. She is easy to get along with, and is quite understanding when you must miss a class. However, some of her material is difficult to understand. I often found myself using Google to look up answers.

Pretty good professor. She's very liberal but is pretty good at hiding her bias. Her lectures can be pretty boring. She decided to drop all exams so all there is to do is a final constitutional 'simulation', that is a lot of fun. Easy A and fairly interesting GE.
Gives great feedback and clearly outlines what she's looking for in her assignments. In class, she's able to moderate debate while not showing much bias toward either side.

I loved her class! She gives great feedback and goes above and beyond for her students. I loved how she makes sure everyone is involved in class discussions, but does not call on people if they do not know the answer. She also lets you use a cheat sheet on the midterm, and you get a take-home final. Be sure to pay attention and take good notes.
one o my favorite professors eve!

Rachel Bowen is an awesome professor, you really learn a lot in her class. If you put in the work, you will get good grades. She offers a lot of help and time if you need it, attending study sessions and asking questions makes the exams and papers easier.
Dr. Bowen is very passionate about Political Science and easily my favorite professor I had while on the Mansfield Campus. Would recommend her classes to anyone!

Very hands on course. She encourages students to be involved and discuss issues during classes. Very helpful if you reach out to her. She also gives bonus points for perfect attendance, and has pretty simple exams. Definitely would take another one of her courses.

I really like her. I think she is tough, but very fair! She makes you think and work for your grade. I found the class to be very interesting. Not a slack off class. I found her to be very helpful answering questions. I would take another of her classes.

Heavy weighted classes. Would not recommend anyone to take her classes. They're boring as is her teaching style and personality. I took two of her classes. She's only there for her research funding. Snobby too, with no reason to be.

Had for Poly Sci 101 & 512. Unprofessional. Class time was half spent discussing readings that had nothing to do with the lecture which followed. Did not use Carmen. Found these classes unchallenging and came out with the same knowledge I had going in. Text books were not wisely chosen.

Professor Bowen was a pretty good instructor and she kept class fun. The only complaint I have is I don't feel like she did a very good job preparing us for the final. Since there were no exams during the quarter, I didn't really know what to expect of the final. Other than that she was great!

Very smart and funny too! I would take another class with her. She is willing to answer questions. She doesn't assign much work but the work she does assign is interesting. She keeps class fun and wants her students to have a good time while learning. A valuable asset to OSU Mansfield!

Makes class fun by mixing lectures with powerpoints, discussions, and debates. Other than the readings, the only assignments all quarter are participating in one debate, 2 3-5 page papers, and the final which she is considering making take home. She likes to keep things interesting and wants you to have a good time. Definitely worth your time!
I didn't watch any of the lectures. I did 20% of the additional readings and did not read the textbook once. I got an A.

This course is super simple. If you have a basic understanding of the US legal system this should be a breeze. Just weekly assignments, three exams, and one 4-6 page paper. If you just complete all the work you should get an A.

I took this class as an online Diversity GE, and it was very interesting! workload is quite manageable each week as well. One thing I will say that exams make up a large portion of your grade, but those are hardly challenging. Other than that, just weekly discussion posts and 1 paper. Great choice for a GE.
Easy class. Workload consisted of no more than a weekly discussion post. Book is recommended but not necessary for the class. Midterms are online and open book and not too hard.

Class was informative but super easy. You get out what you put into it - the lectures and readings are long and interesting, but you really don't need them to do fine with the weekly work. I probably spent like an hour on class each week, plus a couple hours for the final paper. Would recommend.
There were 2 papers, 2 exams and 2 discussion posts every week. Class was easy, but I learned so much! I enhoyed professor Bowes lectures and attitude.

There was one required final paper and 3 exams. There were 2 disscussion posts every week. All exams were extremely easy and open book/note. Professor Bowe was extremely nice and understanding. I enjoyed listening to her lectures.

Professor Bowe was amazing! She's an attorney, so she's very knowledgeable about the subject matter and it shows how much she cares about it. Her class is low-maintenance, just a couple short discussion posts a week, one paper, and non-cumulative open-note exams. Easy A and she was engaging even in online lectures.
Online class so I didn't interact with her much. However she seemed nice and the class is easy.

Such an easy A and she is honestly the best! Her lectures are so interesting and there is an extra credit assignment worth 3%. The 2 papers are relatively easy and she is very willing to help and give feedback if you need it. Definitely recommend!!
An easy online class. Her lectures were thorough and she made sure everything on the quiz or exam was covered in her recorded lectures
